<br>
Here is an example:<br>
<br>
Lets say that there are 6 instances in a single tick making an instant 1 second or so. All 20 pets are sent in on a mob, but due to very difficult timing they are spaced out on the mob per tick with some on the same instance and others not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1 tick</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
instant 1  pet a, pet b, pet c, pet d<br>
instant 2  pet e, pet f,  pet g, pet h<br>
instant 3  pet i,  pet j,  pet k, pet L<br>
instant 4  pet m, pet n, pet o, pet p, pet q,<br>
instant 5  pet r, pet s,<br>
instant 6  pet t<br>
<br>
In the above example only pet q would not be able to hit the mob in the first set of ticks.  Due to casting times on spells and lag and commands given to pets it would be very rare that you will have a bunch of pets stacked on the same instant that a mob can be hit at.<br>
<br>
This may be shown at how fast the mobs fell with 24 pets on them.<br>
<br>
This is just supposition and could be wrong, then again it could be right.<br>
<br>
